Pre-Game Insights: India will face New Zealand in the second T20I match on January 29, 2023, at the Ekana International Cricket Stadium in Lucknow.
New Zealand leads the three-match T20I series 1-0 after winning the first match in Ranchi.
India aims to win the second match to stay in the series.
Hardik Pandya's team might make some changes for the second match.
Prithvi Shaw might open with Shubman Gill, replacing Rahul Tripathi.
Ishan Kishan is likely to be retained due to his wicketkeeping role.
Washington Sundar performed well in the first T20I with 50 runs off 28 balls and 2 wickets.
Arshdeep Singh might be replaced by Mukesh Kumar due to his struggles in the first T20I.
Kuldeep Yadav might be the sole spinner in the playing eleven.
